To plot indicator values, in the OnData event handler, call the Plot method.

private BollingerBands _bb;

// In Initialize()
var symbol = AddEquity("SPY").Symbol;
_bb = BB(symbol, period, k);

// In OnData()
if (_bb.IsReady)
{
    Plot("My Indicators", "standarddeviation", _bb.StandardDeviation.Current.Value);
    Plot("My Indicators", "middleband", _bb.MiddleBand.Current.Value);
    Plot("My Indicators", "upperband", _bb.UpperBand.Current.Value);
    Plot("My Indicators", "lowerband", _bb.LowerBand.Current.Value);
    Plot("My Indicators", "bandwidth", _bb.BandWidth.Current.Value);
    Plot("My Indicators", "percentb", _bb.PercentB.Current.Value);
    Plot("My Indicators", "price", _bb.Price.Current.Value);
    Plot("My Indicators", "bollingerbands", _bb.Current.Value);
}
# In Initialize()
symbol = self.AddEquity("SPY").Symbol
self.bb = self.BB(symbol, period, k)

# In OnData()
if self.bb.IsReady:
    self.Plot("My Indicators", "standarddeviation", self.bb.StandardDeviation.Current.Value)
    self.Plot("My Indicators", "middleband", self.bb.MiddleBand.Current.Value)
    self.Plot("My Indicators", "upperband", self.bb.UpperBand.Current.Value)
    self.Plot("My Indicators", "lowerband", self.bb.LowerBand.Current.Value)
    self.Plot("My Indicators", "bandwidth", self.bb.BandWidth.Current.Value)
    self.Plot("My Indicators", "percentb", self.bb.PercentB.Current.Value)
    self.Plot("My Indicators", "price", self.bb.Price.Current.Value)
    self.Plot("My Indicators", "bollingerbands", self.bb.Current.Value)
